summary.name: Birdstrikes Dataset
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about bird strikes incidents involving aircrafts.

properties.description: Name of the airport where the bird strike occurred.
Make and model of the aircraft involved in the bird strike.
Amount of damage caused by the bird strike.
Date of the flight when the bird strike occurred.
Airline operator of the aircraft involved in the bird strike.
State of origin of the flight.
Phase of flight during which the bird strike occurred.
Size of the wildlife involved in the bird strike.
Species of the wildlife involved in the bird strike.
Time of day when the bird strike occurred.
Other costs associated with the bird strike incident.
Cost of repairing the aircraft after the bird strike.
Total cost of the bird strike incident.
Indicated airspeed (IAS) of the aircraft in knots at the time of the bird strike.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.visualization: bar chart of number of bird strikes per airport
goals.rationale: This helps identify airports with high bird strike incidents and can inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?
goals.visualization: horizontal bar chart of count of bird strikes by aircraft make and model
goals.rationale: This information can be used to inform aircraft maintenance and design decisions to reduce bird strike incidents.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strike damage severity?
goals.visualization: pie chart of proportion of bird strikes by damage severity
goals.rationale: This helps understand the impact of bird strikes on aircraft and can inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the trend of bird strike incidents over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of number of bird strikes by year
goals.rationale: This helps identify if bird strike incidents are increasing or decreasing over time and can inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?
goals.visualization: horizontal bar chart of count of bird strikes by wildlife species
goals.rationale: This information can be used to inform decisions on habitat management and bird control measures to reduce bird strike incidents.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Airport_Name', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport Name')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    aircraft_counts = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().head(10)
    sns.barplot(x=aircraft_counts.values, y=aircraft_counts.index, palette="viridis")
    plt.title("What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Count of Bird Strikes")
    plt.ylabel("Aircraft Make and Model")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    damage_counts = data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(damage_counts, labels=damage_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strike damage severity?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title="Damage Severity", loc="upper left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Flight_Date'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Flight_Date'].dt.year

    yearly_counts = data.groupby('Year').size().reset_index(name='Number_of_Bird_Strikes')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Number_of_Bird_Strikes', data=yearly_counts)
    plt.title('What is the trend of bird strike incidents over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().reset_index()
    data_species_count.columns = ['Wildlife_Species', 'Count']
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='Count', y='Wildlife_Species', data=data_species_count, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Count of Bird Strikes')
    plt.ylabel('Wildlife Species')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
